{
  "texts": [
    "We conducted a modified version of both an MTT and cMTT.",
    "In our MTT, we asked a representative sample of U.S. adults to judge the source of ten pairs of moral evaluative passages.",
    "The passages were human and LLM responses to a question about why a specific description of a human action is wrong or not wrong (see 36).",
    "The actions were pre-classified as wrong either by moral standards or by social convention.",
    "Before instructing them on this test, we asked the same participants to make several judgments about the content of each moral evaluation (e.g., \"Which responder is more morally virtuous?"
  ]
}